article.headline: Colorado 77, TCU 59
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Marcus Hall and Richard Roby each scored 17 points Tuesday night to lead Colorado to a 77-59 victory over TCU. Roby got 15 of his points in the first half, including 11 of the Buffaloes' first 14 points. Colorado, 7-1 and off to its best start since the 1989-90 season, led throughout the game. The Buffaloes opened the second half with an 11-2 run. Chris Copeland added 14 points and Jayson Obazuaye had 13 for the Buffaloes. Nile Murry led TCU (3-7) with 12 points and Brent Hackett added 10. Colorado shot 49 percent from the field and TCU shot 31 percent. Colorado led 36-27 at the half.
